data.title: Nice Find
data.text: After one of our line dancing classes, twelve of us met at the Rendezvous Café & Wine Bar for lunch/brunch.  That was my first visit, and I found the service to be excellent and the food was very good.  I've returned several times since then for late breakfast/early lunch; and, I can highly recommend this café.  The quiche, omelet, side of bacon, chicken salad sandwich and salads are some of my favorite food items.  While I have seen several moms and children there during my daytime visits, I don't think dinner with children would be a good idea.

data.title: Fun spot!
data.text: We enjoy this place for just a glass or wine (or two) but also for their food.  The food is reasonably priced and a nice variety on the menu.  It's a great location and good service too.

data.title: Tapas on the Patio
data.text: My wife and I went last night and decided to eat on the Patio.  What a delight.  The owners obviously pay a lot of attention to the plants and shrubs - just beautiful.  Just like previous visits, the food was great.  Lots of variety to choose from, great service and prices.

data.title: Great for relaxing!
data.text: This is my husband and I's favorite place when it is just the two of us.  A light meal and a glass of wine out on the patio is so relaxing.  The live music is fun, but it can get VERY tight on space and very loud if you are seated indoors on music nights.  We inadvertently went here one night when they had a guest chef doing custom pastas in the adjacent party room and that was fantastic!

data.title: Great Coffee, soup and salads
data.text: Charming cafe/coffee shop with a relaxed atmosphere and delicious food.  Try their soup of the day.  You won't be disappointed. On the weekends they have live music from local artists and a great selection of wine. Staff is very friendly and helpful  They also have a nice meeting room for groups.

data.title: Gotta try!!
data.text: awesome, relaxing atmosphere, awesome food and drink and the owners are nice as can be..If you love wine, café style food and great music, this is it. They have outdoor seating too on nice days.

data.title: Friendly Service
data.text: Good food and friendly service. Prices are a little high, but all in all its worth it. I like the half and half, half sandwich and soup. The Frenchman and the French onion soup are a great combo.

data.title: Always a great time.
data.text: Been coming here since the place opened. Owners are usually there to make sure the party is always a memorable one. Excellent food & deserts along with full wine & beer selection. Great music, sometimes full bands. Never too loud and if comedy is your thing they have that too along with a occasionally murder mystery dinner or wine tasting. Go early they fill up fAst!

data.title: Good light fare and coffee and pastries
data.text: A small place mostly a bistro with coffee, wines, beers, and pastries, good light fare for breakfast and lunch, including chicken salad sandwiches, club sandwiches, muffins, Mimosas, and similar fare.

data.title: Ladies Luncheon
data.text:
I met a group of ladies from my subdivision at the Rendezvous Cafe for lunch last month. I had never been there before. I had the lunch "pick two" special of soup and quiche. They were both obviously homemade and delicious!  I didn't try the desserts but several of the ladies in our group did and were raving over them. They appeared to be homemade as well. 
Many restaurants now say "baked fresh daily", which I'm sure is true, but there is quite a difference between something homemade and something that is institutional and is just "baked" in the restaurant each day. This restaurant seems to have legitimate, "made from scratch" food. If it isn't, it sure takes & looks like it is!

data.title: Great Atmosphere and Coffee!
data.text: I frequent this place with friends, and we love the atmosphere and the coffee! I have not yet bought the food, but my friends have, and it looks incredible. The only reason I'm not giving it 5 stars is because the price is a little steep for food.

data.title: Perfect little gem
data.text: Nice find in OFallon! Tried it for lunch and it was very good. Will def. go back! Great looking desserts, lots of choices for coffee and other drinks, great place for small gathering/party/shower-has separate room for it.

data.title: Pricing themselves out of customers
data.text:
There is now a $15 per person limit when you come to Rendezvous. We were informed by our 
waitress after we sat down.  They serve a wonderful Lobster Bisque and now can only get the bisque on Friday nights. Makes no sense to me to have a good Bisque that customer all want to order and can't. I don't think that's the way to make money or happy customers. The white wine when ordered you must wait while it is chilled. Even chilled whites are never chilled enough. Prices on wine are high. If you buy there a bottle can be $28 but if you to take home $18.

data.title: great Local Spot
data.text: if you like wine come here. Period. Great selection with very reasonable prices. They also have some good local beers. The food I'd very good, we usually get the cheese plate and some tapas. And live music Friday and Saturday. Will be a regular spot for us.

data.title: Relax and enjoy!
data.text: We love visiting Rendezvous, especially if we've had a hectic week. We usually go on Thursday evenings. If you're in a hurry, this is not your place, but if you're looking to relax and forget the workaday world, this is it!

data.title: Wish my town had a place like this.
data.text:
To me, this place is a GEM. A coffee shop/ wine bar that serves delicious food and has live entertainment on the weekends? Yes, please! All my favorite things rolled into one venue. Visiting family, I came here several times in one week. The specialty coffee drinks are consistent and high quality. The wine list is amazingly low priced for the selection. The atmosphere is a perfect blend of cozy and hip with a peaceful garden patio option. 

The cupcakes are so good, my sister had Rendezvous cater her wedding to rave reviews. If I lived here, I'd be a regular. 

Please note, this place is a coffee and wine bar fusion hang out. I'm delighted they have meal options and can accommodate a dinner date, however, this place does not advertise itself to be a traditional Resturant. I imagine some of the poor reviews come from people expecting a regular dining experience. If those people could appreciate an eclectic venue as this place uniquely offers, I imagine they would give it a higher rating. That being said, my brunch dining experience was comparable to any brunch and service I had living in NYC! Seriously, this place rocks.

data.title: Just The Place
data.text: Great place to have a coffee or a meal.  Excellent choice of wines and knowledgeable staff.  Awesome patio with lots of shade.

data.title: Great local restaurant
data.text: I've been here several times with friends.  We enjoy the goat cheese, and trying the different wines they have to offer. The staff is very knowledgable and friendly!

data.title: Great restaurant
data.text: I love this restaurant, the food is great and the people that work there are awesome.  Don't go here if you are in a hurry, but if you want to visit with friends and enjoy a meal, this is the place.

data.title: Valentine's Day dinner disaster
data.text:
$65 a plate for 4 course meal.  
1.  soup was "broken"  the milk curdled in it... ick
2.  salad - was nothing more than bagged field greens and lacked any thing else that they said would be in it.  vinaigrette was lackluster
palate cleanser - I was given a soup spoon to eat sherbet. lol
3.  veil chop was RAW.  pork "chop" was tenderloin.  inconsistent serving sizes between guests;  mine was tiny, thin sliced and COLD!  mashed potatoes were cold, too!    OWNERS took our plates back and MICROWAVED them.   double ick
4. dessert was ok.  mine was fine - til I dug into a spoon ful of raw dough.  hubby's was overcooked. 
This was the worst meal I have ever encountered in a restaurant, much less at that price point.  
it did include wine and champagne upon arrival.  but there was nothing spectacular about the wines and the last course of chocolate cake with dry wine just did not pair well. 
we will never go there again.  
we went to red lobster after spending $130 there so we could have DINNER!  

OH.. and no music in our room... but the main bar had live entertainment.  hmmmm - who was paying all the money?!  ya - the 40 people in the special dining room.
